	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok, now that everyone knows how to get Ronium, everyone wants to know how to get the molds for the Armor of Ro =P<BR>
<BR>
Okie, time for another spoiler, here is how you get every one of the molds for every piece of Ro armor:<BR>
<BR>
Yes, this armor will require faction building, just like the ronium. I'll tell you how to raise faction for the molds that will usually need it.<BR>
<BR>
Getting the molds will require good faction with ALL of the paladin guilds all over Norrath. The place where you receive each of the molds is in The Mountains of Rathe. There is a paladin camp in the north eastern part of Rathe Mountains, where all of the holders of the Armor of Ro reside. The easiest way to find the camp, is to turn RIGHT in Rathe Mountains when coming from the Feerrott zone. Just keep heading straight after you turn right and the paladin camp is near an orc camp up on a hill. If you still have trouble finding it, check out Everlore's map of Rathe Mountains. Nice little camp they have here, you can even buy rations from the vendor =) If you hail one of the paladins there, they will tell you which piece of the armor of Ro they hold. For example, if you hail one of them, and they say they are the holder of the Greaves of Ro, then that is the person that you receive the mold for the Greaves of Ro from. Simple enough (I hope). Now, if you want to find out if your faction is high enough for the Greaves of Ro, after you've hailed the person, say 'what Greaves of Ro'. If your faction is high enough, they will tell you how to (or give you an idea) do the quest for that piece of Ro armor. If your faction isn't high enough... they'll let you know =P<BR>
<BR>
So now you know where to go to get the quest for the molds, and how to find out if your faction is high enough.<BR>
<BR>
There are 7 different pieces to the armor of Ro. They are as follows:<BR>
- Breastplate of Ro<BR>
- Greaves of Ro<BR>
- Helm of Ro<BR>
- Vambraces of Ro<BR>
- Boots of Ro<BR>
- Bracer of Ro<BR>
- Gauntlets of Ro<BR>
<BR>
The only faction problems I had was with the Bracer of Ro, and the Vambraces of Ro. They are VERY annoying quests. I will only be telling you how to raise faction with those two, if you have problems with other factions... e-mail me, or figure it out yourself, it shouldn't be very hard.<BR>
<BR>
Here is how you obtain the molds for each piece of Ro armor:<BR>
<BR>
-=Breastplate of Ro=-<BR>
You need 2 dark cauldrons from Castle Mistmoore. This is definitely the hardest piece of Ro armor to get, because, yes, once again you have to stay in Mistmoore for awhile. Yeah I know we all hate Castle Mistmoore, but for some reason Verant wants us pallies to spend some time there. The dark cauldrons are NO DROP(ugh), so yeppers, you gotta go in the castle with some friends. A group of mid 30's would be fine. The dark cauldrons come from the ancille cooks, and are an uncommon drop. Get a group that knows what they're doing and getting these should be a cinch. I had a level 50 monk pulling for me so it was a breeze =) (you rock Gostfaas!). Once you get both the cauldrons, head to the pally camp in Rathe Mountains and turn them into the Breastplate of Ro guy(or gal), and they'll reward you with the mold for the Breastplate of Ro(if your faction is high enough =P).<BR>
<BR>
-=Greaves of Ro=-<BR>
You need 1 head from a nightfall giant. Nightfall giants are a semi-rare spawn in west(?) commonlands, and only come out at night(go figure). They are just as hard as regular hill giants, and I'm not sure if they drop the heads every time... I would imagine they do. The head is NOT no drop(woohoo!) so you can buy them from other greedy players.<BR>
<BR>
-=Helm of Ro=-<BR>
This one is pretty tough... you need 2 undead cyclops skulls. The undead cyclops spawn in South Ro, and are about as hard as normal cyclops'. I'm not sure on the spawn frequency of them... I think they are semi-rare. I'm pretty sure they drop the skulls every time though. Good thing they are undead, makes it easier for us pallies to take em down. The skulls are NOT no drop, so you can buy them off players.<BR>
<BR>
-=Vambraces of Ro=-<BR>
You will not like this one. You will probably need to raise your faction with the Qeynos paladin guild. In order to do this, go to north Qeynos and wait for Lashun Novashine to come out (he shouts when he comes out so you'll know). After you see him, hail him and make him stop. Give him 2(?... maybe 3) pieces of gold, and your faction with the Qeynos cleric and paladin guilds will go up. Note: this takes FOREVER, and you can't give him like 100 pieces of gold to make your faction go up quicker, you have to give him just 2(or 3) at a time, I'm pretty sure its 2. You will end up dumping a TON of gold on to this guy, but it works. Once you think you've given him enough gold, go check if your faction is high enough by talking to the Vambraces of Ro lady at the pally camp in Rathe Mountains. Once you've gotten your faction up, she tells you to kill diseased sharks in the oceans of Qeynos. Here's the fun part =\ You need 2 rotted shark meats from the plague sharks in Erud's Crossing. The plague sharks are a semi-rare spawn, and are VERY hard to find. You can't track them, they're too fast. If you actually see it, it will get away before you have time to attack (unless you root it in time). The only way to find and kill these is if 1. its stuck at the beach, which happens very rarely, or 2. you take the Seaking. If the plague shark is up, it will ALWAYS be right underneath the ship Seaking when it is coming from North Qeynos or Erudin. So hop on the Seaking, and right after you zone into Erud's Crossing, jump off and follow it. You will see the plague shark if its up. Root his ass and kill him. Plague sharks are about level 35, and fight VERY mean. They aren't as hard as killer sharks (which are nearly frigging impossible), but they will hit pretty hard, and fast, and to add insult to injury, their attack procs cancel magic. Note: it is VERY helpful to have a caster with you, especially a druid, who can heal/snare/nuke. So you've killed the plague shark, hooray! You go over to loot it, expecting to find a rotted shark meat, and whats this? Nothing. Yep, its an uncommon drop. So get back on that Seaking and wait for the plague shark to spawn again (fun =P). Rinse and repeat until you've obtained 2 rotted shark meats. The rotted shark meat is NOT no drop, so you could buy them from players... but seriously, who is going to have one.<BR>
<BR>
-=Boots of Ro=-<BR>
Woohoo, finally an easy one. Kill a rare spawn in South Ro named Sandgiant Hussam. He is pretty wussy, despite his looking like a normal sand giant. He is about mid 20ish, and drops what you need every time, which are the Kilij Plans. It may be awhile before you see this guy, he is a pretty rare spawn, all you need is one kilij plans though. Kilij plans are NOT no drop, so you can buy them off players.<BR>
<BR>
-=Bracer of Ro=-<BR>
You're not gonna like this one either. First of all, you need high-amiable faction with the Erudite paladin guild. What? Erudite paladin guild? Well how in the world do I get good faction with that? Actually, its pretty easy. Go to Toxxulia Forest, you'll find docks on the lake (The Wasty Deep), but no boats come there or anything. Next to the docks a level 7 or 8 necromancer npc(Elial Brooks?) is standing there. Kill him (very wussy), and your faction will go up with the Erudite paladin guild. Wait for him to spawn again, not really sure on spawn time (forgot), probably around 20 minutes. Kill him at least 5 times and your faction should be good enough to do the quest. You need 2 nets from the goblin netmasters in Lake Rathetear. The goblin netmasters are a pretty rare spawn, about every 2 or 3 hours one spawns. They are about level 35, and are wizards, so they nuke, but their low hp makes up for the nukes, and they suck at melee, though hit pretty hard (mid 70's). But they have one very annoying feature... they have a tendancy to commit suicide, leaving no corpse. If you see one, ROOT IT, and kill it IN the water. DO NOT BRING THEM TO SHORE, unless you have a necro/sk/druid/ranger who can SNARE them. If they are snared, they will not suicide on you, but you should snare them IN the water, before you bring it to shore. If they are not snared, and you attempt to pull it to shore and kill it... it will be gone before you know it. So if you intend on soloing one, kill it IN the water. You should be able to solo one without lay hands at level 39. The nets are NO DROP, so YOU have to loot them.<BR>
<BR>
-=Gauntlets of Ro=-<BR>
This one is pretty easy. You need 1 locket from Sentry Alchin (spelling?) in South Karana. Sentry Alchin isn't TOO hard of a kill... but don't intend on solo ing him until your at least 39. He drops the locket every time, but its NO DROP, so you gotta loot it. He isn't a very rare spawn either, and I'm pretty sure he's a random spawn. People will usually shout if they see him, but there are usually other players after him =(<BR>
<BR>
If your STILL confused about where you take the things to turn them in to receive the molds, which I explained earlier, I'll explain it again. You take the item that you need for the certain piece of Ro armor to the paladin camp in Rathe Mountains. Who do I give it to? Well, even I can't recall all the names of the people there, and which piece of Ro armor they hold. So talk to them! Hail them, and they'll tell you which piece of Ro armor's mold they have! Ask them about the armor if you would like to know if your faction is high enough, they will tell you how to do the quest if your faction is high enough. They will tell you to get lost if it isn't. Simple enough, if you're still confused, then too bad.<BR>
<BR>
How to make your Ro armor:<BR>
Take the mold, and the bar of ronium to ANY forge in one of the cities. Make sure your blacksmithing skill is at least 1 (train it at your guildmaster), or I can't gurantee it will work. Put the bar of Ronium, and the mold into the forge and click combine. You've created a piece of Ro armor. All Ro armor is not no drop =)<BR>
Have fun, and good luck, and don't give up! =P<BR>
<BR>
Seijuro Hiko &lt;Order of BlackWatch&gt;<BR>
Paladin of the 48th circle<BR>
Servant to Karana<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
