			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I also would like to thank Seijuro Hiko for the information he provided, although I would like to say that while doing the bracer quests I was able to solo the netmasters (who are shadow nights) at lvl 30.  They do use harm touch right away and I was also able to pull them onto land without them poofing.  The easiest way to find them is to sit on the northwestern island (1 spawn I think it's called).  They swim right past the eastern side of the island and you can stand in the water so that you can see clearly and you can wait for them to swim by.  <BR>
<BR>
Also the quest for Sentry Alchien isn't all that hard like Seijuro said but you either have to follow him around until he turns into a werewolf or you kill him in his human form which causes you to take a large faction hit with Qeynos, it took me from kindly to amible.  (and I have seen 2 Alchiens in the zone at the same time so he is always wondering around you just have to fine him)<BR>
<BR>
Last but not least, Gunlok isn't really in the pally guild, he stays outside the door to the guild hall. (His approx loc is pos1300, pos175)<BR>
<BR>

